<br>
Mobs start summoning when a certain amount of HP has been taken from it, thus any mob (unless otherwise coded) can be debuffed to wazoo on INC or before inc without summoning people. Once damage is done to it though, it will still summon the top people on it's aggro list, which happen to be the debuffers, aka chanter. It's also why some monks prefer to run by mobs to get aggro, as opposed to throwing a star or something at the mob...so they don't get summoned trying to pull mobs and instead can outrun the mob, then FD.<br>
<br>
And as to the first poster, it could be because epic is lower level and has low level aggro attached to it. I don't think they coded the pets themselves any differently. Epic, as stated before, also has more procs to keep aggro, which coincidently happen to have a stun component with them (aggro city). It's no suprise to me that the epic holds aggro better than PoP pets.<br>
