If a summoning mob is damaged enough by ANY means, it will begin to summon those on it's hate list, top to bottom, one at a time.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zyphyr>Zyphyr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 750<br> <font color=#333333>(12/24/02 9:49:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoP pets VS Epic and agro on multiple mobs</span><hr size=1> Being rather tired of this whole debate, I decided to actually do some testing with regards to DS agro and recruited a friend to help.<br>
<br>
Test Conditions:<br>
PC 1 = Level 22 Magician using Sheild of Flame (8 point DS)<br>
PC 2 = Level 22 Enchanter using summoned Throwing Daggers<br>
<br>
Location = Paludal Caverns<br>
Server = Test<br>
<br>
Test Mobs = Plerg fiends<br>
<br>
Test Method = Magician walks near fiend with the DS on. After mob has hit the DS, enchanter throws daggers until fiend switches targets. After mob switches, we kill it off.<br>
<br>
Test was performed 4 times.<br>
<br>
Test 1 = 4 Hits on DS (32 damage), 2 dagger throws (miss, 3 points) before fiend switches.<br>
Test 2 = 3 Hits on DS (24 damage), 1 throw (2 points)<br>
Test 3 = 6 Hits on DS (64 damage), 3 throws (miss,miss, 4 points)<br>
Test 4 = 4 Hits on DS (24 damage), 1 throw (5 points)<br>
<br>
<br>
Conclusion : If the damage from a DS generates any agro at all, it is so low as to be unmeasurable.<br>
<br>
<br>
We would have done more tests, but those characters are essentially naked (we stopped playing them after the Great Test Server Equipment Wipe and returned to playing our production server characters) which really slowed us down. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:medium;">Zyphyr Runnersbane</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
