<br>
1) Rampage IS NOT determined by how high you are on the hate list, so casting a DS on the tank and getting rampage doesn't prove it is super high aggro.<br>
<br>
2) The monk is summoned because the mob is damaged.  The mob is damaged because of the DS.  Take this for example.<br>
<br>
Scenario 1<br>
<br>
Monk pulls mob with prox aggro.<br>
Top of the hate list: Monk<br>
Summons: Nobody<br>
<br>
Monk gets hit on the way back and the mob loses X amount of health and starts summoning.<br>
Top of the hate list: Monk<br>
Summons: Monk<br>
<br>
Scenario 2<br>
<br>
Monk pulls mob with prox aggro.<br>
Top of the hate list: Monk<br>
Summons: Nobody<br>
<br>
Monk gets to camp without being hit and Warrior starts attacking the mob, and reaches the top of the hate list.<br>
Top of the hate list: WARRIOR<br>
Summons: WARRIOR<br>
<br>
So, the reason that monks sometimes do not want DS on a pull isn't because of aggro, it's because if they get hit enough the mob will start to summon.<br>
<br>
Now, if I had pet hold I'd log in right now and put this silly argument to an end (since you should usually DS your pet and the tank anyways).  Since I don't, I'll rely on someone else. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8548" target="top">Gamrok Lazyarse</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
